From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Mon, 22 Jun 2026 13:24:52 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] uu_seq: add injected-I/O logical entry for an in-process
 brush builtin
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adapt vendored uu_seq to run as a native in-process brush builtin reading/
writing the shell's logical OpenFile sink/source instead of process-global
stdio — no process-global stdio, no dup2, pipeline-safe. Diagnostics are routed
to the logical stderr (or accumulated and returned), exit codes returned (no
show!/set_exit_code/process::exit). uumain retained as a thin descriptor bridge.
Behavior kept byte-for-byte; only the I/O seam moved.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01TNBGBV51j5AH4j8k8ENi1W
---
 Cargo.lock | 1464 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 src/seq.rs |  143 ++++-
 2 files changed, 1597 insertions(+), 10 deletions(-)
 create mode 100644 engine/vendor/uu_seq/Cargo.lock

